'''Edson Bindilatti''' (born March 13, 1979 in [[Bahia]], [[Brazil]]<ref>[http://www.sochi2014.com/en/athlete-edson-bindilatti Sochi 2014]</ref>) is a [[decathlete]] and [[bobsledder]] from [[Brazil]]. He competed for [[Brazil at the 2014 Winter Olympics]] in the [[Bobsleigh at the 2014 Winter Olympics <U+2013> Four-man|four-man]] competition<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.brasil.gov.br/esporte/2014/01/comite-olimpico-inscreve-13-atletas-em-sochi-2014 |title=Comit<U+00EA> Ol<U+00ED>mpico inscreve 13 atletas em Sochi 2014|trans_title=Olympic Committee inscribed 13 athletes in Sochi 2014 |language=[[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] |date=31 January 2014 |website=http://www.brasil.gov.br/|publisher=[[Brazilian Government]]|accessdate=31 January 2014}}</ref> where he placed in 29th position out of 30 teams along with ([[F<U+00E1>bio Gon<U+00E7>alves Silva]], [[Edson Martins]] and [[Odirlei Pessoni]]).<ref>[http://www.sochi2014.com/en/bobsleigh-four-man-heat-4 Final 4 man bobsled results at Sochi 2014]</ref> He also competed for Brazil at the [[2002 Winter Olympics|2002]] and [[2006 Winter Olympics]].

